lexUnit.name: squirt.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: (with reference to a liquid) be or cause to be ejected in a thin jet from a small opening.

sentence.text: This spotted sea hare ( above ) is a mollusc that can squirt a cloud of purple ink into the water in response to the approach of a predator .
He crouched behind the mother to squirt milk into the bottle .
A handsome Irish youth with ginger hair squirted some boiling water into the teapot and swilled a cup of dark brown liquid into a chipped cup .

One thinks of the stories of child muggers bearing sharp knives , driven below by a greater police presence upstairs , of the Underground ` acid fiend " who squirts hydrochloric acid on people 's legs before making his escape , of steamers , hip-hop-styled persons perpetrating economy-sized thefts .
Most species also squirt the oil at intruders as a form of defence so that the ground around the nest becomes impregnated with it .
Needing something light and refreshing to slake a newly parched mouth and throat , she squirted soda from a siphon into a tall glass and added a cluster of ice cubes .
So Daedalus is squirting one such solution through small round nozzles into the other .
A milkman who was temporarily blinded when superglue was squirted into his eyes , has given up his job .
She 'd read that when an elephant has a wound , the mahout squirts chilli juice in its eyes by way of distraction .
It is a superbly efficient food gatherer , and can siphon ten gallons of water at a single suck and squirt this into the elephant 's mouth .
Juron squirted his water canteen into that arid gob again and again .
A man who had superglue squirted in his face by muggers may have lost the sight of one eye .
Surprisingly , it 's normal for some women to squirt out a fluid at the moment of orgasm .
Some fruit-eating birds can swallow fruit and only five minutes later squirt out the remains .
